# •  ~/.local/bin/terminal-theme-switcher  — switches the theme. By default it follows
# your macOS appearance (light/dark mode). You can also force one with  terminal-theme-
# switcher dark  or  light .
# •  ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.lilac.terminal-theme-switcher.plist  — a launchd agent
# that runs the script at 7:00 AM (light) and 7:00 PM (dark), plus on login.

# Since it reads macOS appearance, it will also match if you use the system's automatic
# light/dark schedule. Edit the  Hour  values in the plist if you want different switch
# times.

!.local/

!.local/bin/
!.local/bin/terminal-theme-switcher

!.local/bin/metadata_never_index.sh

